Yeah.

1055
01:00:49,698 --> 01:00:53,034
Take a look at this.
I don't understand it.

1056
01:00:53,034 --> 01:00:54,494
Charles was
an excellent doctor.

1057
01:00:54,494 --> 01:00:56,036
Why would he
try and kill himself...

1058
01:00:56,036 --> 01:00:58,497
with a thousand milligrams
of stool softener?

1059
01:00:58,497 --> 01:01:00,248
He tried to kill himself
with a laxative?

1060
01:01:00,248 --> 01:01:01,834
That and 800 milligrams...

1061
01:01:01,834 --> 01:01:03,711
of a nonsteroidal
anti-inflammatory.

1062
01:01:03,711 --> 01:01:06,045
That's for menstrual cramps.

1063
01:01:06,045 --> 01:01:07,130
I know.

1064
01:01:07,130 --> 01:01:09,466
Antihistamines,
aspirins, muscle relaxants...

1065
01:01:09,466 --> 01:01:12,177
vitamin tablets...
all in small dosages.

1066
01:01:12,177 --> 01:01:14,471
I don't get it.

1067
01:01:14,471 --> 01:01:16,972
Your brother...

1068
01:01:16,972 --> 01:01:20,684
wasn't he doing immunization
work in South America?

1069
01:01:20,684 --> 01:01:22,227
Yes.

1070
01:01:23,395 --> 01:01:24,896
He was brilliant.

1071
01:01:24,896 --> 01:01:28,274
Then he would have had access
to some very lethal medications.

1072
01:01:28,274 --> 01:01:31,694
I know. So why would he
take that stuff?

1073
01:01:31,694 --> 01:01:34,363
It's like he raided
somebody's medicine chest.

1074
01:01:34,363 --> 01:01:36,198
You might as well know.

1075
01:01:36,198 --> 01:01:38,492
I don't think that Charles
committed suicide.

1076
01:01:38,492 --> 01:01:40,202
What?

1077
01:01:40,202 --> 01:01:42,496
Harry, why do you say that?

1078
01:01:42,496 --> 01:01:44,997
For one thing, there was
scar tissue on the heart.

1079
01:01:44,997 --> 01:01:48,000
That usually indicates
a heart attack.

1080
01:01:48,000 --> 01:01:49,210
Heart attack.

1081
01:01:49,210 --> 01:01:52,171
Also, there were some signs
of sexual activity.

1082
01:01:56,216 --> 01:01:58,384
What about the suicide note?

1083
01:01:58,384 --> 01:02:00,386
That's the only thing
I can't understand...

1084
01:02:00,386 --> 01:02:02,347
because the lab reports
came back...

1085
01:02:02,347 --> 01:02:04,348
and the drugs that Charles took
are all highly suspect.

1086
01:02:04,348 --> 01:02:07,142
What's wrong
with the drugs he took?

1087
01:02:07,142 --> 01:02:08,769
Can't they kill you?

1088
01:02:08,769 --> 01:02:10,687
They'll give you the runs,
numb your ovaries...

1089
01:02:10,687 --> 01:02:12,648
and give you a very relaxed take
on your situation...

1090
01:02:12,648 --> 01:02:14,315
but they won't kill you.

1091
01:02:14,315 --> 01:02:17,944
I don't see why you have to
turn this into a police case.

1092
01:02:17,944 --> 01:02:19,445
Charles is dead.

1093
01:02:19,445 --> 01:02:22,824
Why don't you just let it be
and bury the man?

1094
01:02:22,824 --> 01:02:24,449
I can't, Marjorie.
I can't bury him...

1095
01:02:24,449 --> 01:02:26,368
until I find out
what happened.

1096
01:02:36,669 --> 01:02:38,170
Hi, Jeanine.

1097
01:02:38,170 --> 01:02:39,672
Hi. How you doing?

1098
01:02:39,672 --> 01:02:41,173
Good. Come on in.

1099
01:02:41,173 --> 01:02:42,675
I brought you something.

1100
01:02:42,675 --> 01:02:44,175
You didn't have to
bring anything.

1101
01:02:44,175 --> 01:02:45,468
I made a whole dinner.

1102
01:02:45,468 --> 01:02:48,179
No, it's not food.
It's a scavenger.

1103
01:02:48,179 --> 01:02:50,682
Take care of
any algae problems.

1104
01:02:50,682 --> 01:02:52,183
Where's your tank?

1105
01:02:52,183 --> 01:02:54,143
Right over there.
It's a bowl, actually.

1106
01:02:54,143 --> 01:02:55,644
A scavenger, huh?

1107
01:02:55,644 --> 01:02:58,689
That's great, because sometimes
I get a little algae.

1108
01:02:58,689 --> 01:03:00,190
A little?

1109
01:03:00,190 --> 01:03:02,192
That's very sweet of you.

1110
01:03:02,192 --> 01:03:04,694
This guy's going to have
a good time tonight.

1111
01:03:04,694 --> 01:03:06,279
I'm just going
to float him.

1112
01:03:06,279 --> 01:03:08,990
Let him get used
to the temperature.

1113
01:03:08,990 --> 01:03:10,616
Where's your brother?

1114
01:03:10,616 --> 01:03:13,618
I don't know. I don't even know
if he's coming.

1115
01:03:13,618 --> 01:03:16,163
But dinner's all ready.
Maybe we should just eat.

1116
01:03:16,163 --> 01:03:17,956
Relax.
He's just a little late.

1117
01:03:17,956 --> 01:03:20,542
Besides, I like it
when we're alone together.

1118
01:03:23,627 --> 01:03:27,631
I wanted you to meet
my brother up front.

1119
01:03:27,631 --> 01:03:29,175
Here, sit down.

1120
01:03:29,175 --> 01:03:31,635
I didn't want you to think...

1121
01:03:31,635 --> 01:03:34,637
that I was keeping
anything from you.

1122
01:03:34,637 --> 01:03:37,640
What would you
be keeping from me?

1123
01:03:37,640 --> 01:03:39,642
My brother.

1124
01:03:39,642 --> 01:03:41,186
What's wrong with him?

1125
01:03:41,186 --> 01:03:42,645
Nothing.
It's just that...

1126
01:03:42,645 --> 01:03:46,190
sometimes he has a hard time
holding onto a job...

1127
01:03:46,190 --> 01:03:47,649
or paying a bill.

1128
01:03:47,649 --> 01:03:49,193
I love spaghetti.

1129
01:03:49,193 --> 01:03:50,652
It's my specialty.

1130
01:03:50,652 --> 01:03:53,654
It's not that
my brother is lazy.

1131
01:03:53,654 --> 01:03:56,199
It's just that he isn't...

1132
01:03:56,199 --> 01:03:57,868
Isn't as accomplished as you?

1133
01:03:57,868 --> 01:03:59,327
That's not it.

1134
01:03:59,327 --> 01:04:02,413
Actually, I wish
he was more like you.

1135
01:04:02,413 --> 01:04:03,663
Do you know that...

1136
01:04:03,663 --> 01:04:06,625
you're the most independent
woman I've ever met...

1137
01:04:06,625 --> 01:04:08,418
that liked me back.

1138
01:04:08,418 --> 01:04:11,129
I know what it's like...

1139
01:04:11,129 --> 01:04:13,631
to be following
in someone's footsteps...

1140
01:04:13,631 --> 01:04:16,133
who is always doing
the right thing...

1141
01:04:16,133 --> 01:04:19,136
and constantly being judged
by their standards.

1142
01:04:19,136 --> 01:04:22,139
Maybe I am judging him
by my standards.

1143
01:04:22,139 --> 01:04:24,432
I'm sure your brother
would love to be like you...

1144
01:04:24,432 --> 01:04:26,351
but it doesn't sound
like he is.

1145
01:04:26,351 --> 01:04:29,270
That's it. For years,
I've hated feeling...

1146
01:04:29,270 --> 01:04:31,272
like I had to take
care of him.

1147
01:04:31,272 --> 01:04:34,066
Don't take care of him.
Just be his brother.

1148
01:04:34,066 --> 01:04:38,654
You're right.
That's what I've got to do.

1149
01:04:39,655 --> 01:04:41,240
Let's eat.

1150
01:04:41,240 --> 01:04:44,158
You don't really need
to meet my brother.

1151
01:04:44,158 --> 01:04:47,662
Just like you don't really have
to meet my sister.

1152
01:04:51,165 --> 01:04:52,499
Feed me.

1153
01:04:52,499 --> 01:04:54,668
Yes, ma'am.

1154
01:04:54,668 --> 01:04:57,171
You want sausage,
or do you want meatballs?

1155
01:04:57,171 --> 01:04:58,171
Both.

1156
01:04:58,171 --> 01:04:59,422
You got it.

1157
01:04:59,422 --> 01:05:01,174
Wilbur...

1158
01:05:01,174 --> 01:05:05,594
what's your feeling
on this prank call?

1159
01:05:05,594 --> 01:05:08,055
Your gut feeling?

1160
01:05:08,055 --> 01:05:09,598
It's nothing, I guess.

1161
01:05:09,598 --> 01:05:15,270
Wilbur, go with your gut.
Remember how often it's right.

1162
01:05:24,278 --> 01:05:26,071
Wilbur?

1163
01:05:26,071 --> 01:05:28,407
Wilbur?

1164
01:05:28,407 --> 01:05:33,411
Yeah. I'm sorry to wake you,
but I'm in jail.

1165
01:05:33,411 --> 01:05:34,871
I've turned myself in.

1166
01:05:34,871 --> 01:05:36,038
What for?

1167
01:05:37,582 --> 01:05:39,083
I killed a man.

1168
01:05:39,083 --> 01:05:40,460
What?

1169
01:05:40,460 --> 01:05:44,296
It was by accident,
but he's dead.

1170
01:05:44,296 --> 01:05:45,589
Dead?

1171
01:05:45,589 --> 01:05:47,090
What? What is it?

1172
01:05:47,090 --> 01:05:48,592
It's nothing.

1173
01:05:48,592 --> 01:05:50,594
Did you say that you...

1174
01:05:50,594 --> 01:05:51,927
Yeah.

1175
01:05:51,927 --> 01:05:55,598
I was in a hotel room
doing an installation...

1176
01:05:55,598 --> 01:05:57,099
and things went bad.

1177
01:05:57,099 --> 01:05:58,767
Oh, my god.
The hotel room.

1178
01:05:58,767 --> 01:06:00,102
That's my prank call!

1179
01:06:00,102 --> 01:06:03,104
The man's name
was Charles Turner.

1180
01:06:03,104 --> 01:06:04,564
I didn't even know him.

1181
01:06:04,564 --> 01:06:08,693
Oh, my god! You?
That was you?

1182
01:06:08,693 --> 01:06:10,403
I need a lawyer,
if you know any.

1183
01:06:10,403 --> 01:06:12,404
I hate to keep
leaning on you...

1184
01:06:12,404 --> 01:06:15,240
but I don't know how I'm going
to find one from in here.

1185
01:06:15,240 --> 01:06:17,117
Yeah, yeah.
I'll take care of it.

1186
01:06:17,117 --> 01:06:18,535
Great.

1187
01:06:18,535 --> 01:06:24,040
Will, I'm sorry.
When I get out of here...

1188
01:06:24,040 --> 01:06:26,043
after I've served my time...

1189
01:06:26,043 --> 01:06:28,753
I'm going to be
the greatest salesman ever...

1190
01:06:28,753 --> 01:06:32,339
and I'm going to pay you back
all the money I owe you.

1191
01:06:32,339 --> 01:06:33,548
OK?

1192
01:06:33,548 --> 01:06:35,050
OK.

1193
01:06:35,050 --> 01:06:37,469
I love you, Will.

1194
01:06:37,469 --> 01:06:39,054
Yeah. Right.

1195
01:06:48,062 --> 01:06:50,064
I know who killed Charles.

1196
01:06:50,064 --> 01:06:51,564
You do?

1197
01:06:51,564 --> 01:06:53,066
This is very difficult.

1198
01:06:53,066 --> 01:06:57,570
Look, Wilbur, this has nothing
to do with us. Really.

1199
01:06:57,570 --> 01:07:00,573
I know you're nothing
like your brother...

1200
01:07:00,573 --> 01:07:03,575
just like I'm nothing
like my sister. Nothing at all.

1201
01:07:03,575 --> 01:07:05,078
Jeanine...

1202
01:07:05,078 --> 01:07:07,079
I know, but it was
an accident.

1203
01:07:07,079 --> 01:07:09,331
There's a lot
at stake here, Wilbur.

1204
01:07:09,331 --> 01:07:11,457
How do you know?
You don't even know Nick.

1205
01:07:11,457 --> 01:07:12,458
Nick?

1206
01:07:12,458 --> 01:07:14,085
My brother.
He killed Charles.

1207
01:07:14,085 --> 01:07:15,129
What?

1208
01:07:15,129 --> 01:07:18,089
It was an accident.
He turned himself in.

1209
01:07:18,089 --> 01:07:20,550
That's why he didn't
show up for dinner.

1210
01:07:20,550 --> 01:07:24,094
He's in jail.
My little brother's in jail.

1211
01:07:24,094 --> 01:07:29,933
Wait a minute, now.
Just calm down, Wilbur.

1212
01:07:29,933 --> 01:07:31,976
I got to get a lawyer
and get him out.

1213
01:07:31,976 --> 01:07:33,978
He can't stay in jail.
He's not streetwise.

1214
01:07:33,978 --> 01:07:36,480
He could get killed in there.

1215
01:07:36,480 --> 01:07:38,691
How did you know
it was an accident?

1216
01:07:40,109 --> 01:07:43,111
I don't know.
I just thought...

1217
01:07:43,111 --> 01:07:46,614
I don't know.
You said that it was.

1218
01:07:46,614 --> 01:07:49,117
I got to find a lawyer.

1219
01:07:49,117 --> 01:07:50,618
What about you?

1220
01:07:50,618 --> 01:07:53,120
What about becoming
chief of police?

1221
01:07:53,120 --> 01:07:55,498
Five minutes ago, I wanted to be
chief of police...

1222
01:07:55,498 --> 01:07:57,332
more than anything
else in the world.

1223
01:07:57,332 --> 01:07:59,334
All the times
that he needed help...

1224
01:07:59,334 --> 01:08:01,002
I helped him because
I felt I had to.

1225
01:08:01,002 --> 01:08:02,086
Now I want to!

1226
01:08:02,086 --> 01:08:04,006
I don't care
if he did it or not.

1227
01:08:04,006 --> 01:08:05,923
He's my brother.
Screw the job.

1228
01:08:12,554 --> 01:08:14,265
Harry?

1229
01:08:14,265 --> 01:08:15,557
Yeah?

1230
01:08:19,060 --> 01:08:21,604
Honey, where have you
been all night?

1231
01:08:21,604 --> 01:08:24,900
At the lab, and then
at the police station.

1232
01:08:24,900 --> 01:08:28,903
What were you doing
at the police station?

1233
01:08:28,903 --> 01:08:30,361
Is there any coffee?

1234
01:08:30,361 --> 01:08:31,362
Yeah.

1235
01:08:33,031 --> 01:08:34,408
Anybody home?

1236
01:08:34,408 --> 01:08:35,492
In here.

1237
01:08:35,492 --> 01:08:37,577
What are they doing here?

1238
01:08:37,577 --> 01:08:38,953
I've called a family meeting.

1239
01:08:38,953 --> 01:08:40,370
What for?

1240
01:08:40,370 --> 01:08:42,122
Your front door was open.

1241
01:08:42,122 --> 01:08:43,207
So?

1242
01:08:43,207 --> 01:08:44,626
Do you want coffee?

1243
01:08:44,626 --> 01:08:45,751
Sure.

1244
01:08:45,751 --> 01:08:46,710
Please.

1245
01:08:48,295 --> 01:08:51,923
Don't move.
I'll make it.

1246
01:08:51,923 --> 01:08:54,426
This isn't going
to take long, I hope.

1247
01:08:54,426 --> 01:08:56,803
I've got two back-to-back
pap smears at 9:00.

1248
01:08:56,803 --> 01:08:58,930
No, it's not.
I just want to wait...

1249
01:08:58,930 --> 01:09:01,139
until mother and dad get here
to explain.

1250
01:09:01,139 --> 01:09:03,351
I don't want to have
to say it twice.

1251
01:09:03,351 --> 01:09:06,311
Your front door is open.

1252
01:09:06,311 --> 01:09:09,648
Iris left it open.

1253
01:09:09,648 --> 01:09:12,441
What's the big news?

1254
01:09:14,069 --> 01:09:15,945
Sit down.

1255
01:09:20,573 --> 01:09:22,575
I've been working
with the police...

1256
01:09:22,575 --> 01:09:25,578
on Charles' case,
as you all probably know, and...

1257
01:09:27,956 --> 01:09:29,790
We've found a murder suspect.

1258
01:09:33,586 --> 01:09:35,087
You did?

1259
01:09:35,087 --> 01:09:36,588
Who was it?

1260
01:09:36,588 --> 01:09:38,173
A salesman.

1261
01:09:38,173 --> 01:09:41,426
What kind of a salesman
would kill Charles?

1262
01:09:41,426 --> 01:09:43,929
A blinds salesman.

1263
01:09:43,929 --> 01:09:45,263
How could a blind salesman...

1264
01:09:45,263 --> 01:09:47,974
No, he sold blinds, dad...

1265
01:09:47,974 --> 01:09:51,268
and he dropped them
on Charles' head.

1266
01:09:52,770 --> 01:09:55,397
He claims it was an accident.

1267
01:09:55,397 --> 01:09:56,565
Oh, lord!

1268
01:09:56,565 --> 01:09:57,899
How do you know all this?

1269
01:09:57,899 --> 01:10:01,610
He turned himself in, confessed.
He even apologized.

1270
01:10:01,610 --> 01:10:03,113
He confessed?

1271
01:10:03,113 --> 01:10:04,530
Yeah.

1272
01:10:04,530 --> 01:10:06,031
What about the suicide?

1273
01:10:06,031 --> 01:10:08,117
This guy said he panicked...

1274
01:10:08,117 --> 01:10:10,034
and set it up to look
like Charles killed himself.

1275
01:10:10,034 --> 01:10:12,580
Oh, my lord!
He said that?

1276
01:10:12,580 --> 01:10:17,125
Harry said he confessed.
That's what confessed means.

1277
01:10:17,125 --> 01:10:18,626
I knew it.

1278
01:10:18,626 --> 01:10:21,462
I knew my Charles would never
take his own life.

1279
01:10:23,214 --> 01:10:25,841
Marjorie, I've got to
talk to you alone!

1280
01:10:25,841 --> 01:10:27,426
Jeanine, not now.

1281
01:10:27,426 --> 01:10:29,260
My boyfriend's brother
is in jail.

1282
01:10:29,260 --> 01:10:30,928
Jeanine, I said not now!

1283
01:10:30,928 --> 01:10:33,182
He is in jail
for killing Charles!

1284
01:10:34,640 --> 01:10:36,267
Wait.

1285
01:10:36,267 --> 01:10:38,519
Wait.
What are you saying?

1286
01:10:38,519 --> 01:10:40,771
That your boyfriend's brother
killed my brother?

1287
01:10:41,856 --> 01:10:44,441
Wait a minute. Your boyfriend
is Nick's brother?

1288
01:10:44,441 --> 01:10:46,443
Nick? I didn't
say his name.

1289
01:10:46,443 --> 01:10:48,695
- How do you know his name?
- How do you know Nick?

1290
01:10:48,695 --> 01:10:50,571
I always thought
she was too sweet...

1291
01:10:50,571 --> 01:10:52,074
not to be hiding
something.

1292
01:10:52,074 --> 01:10:54,617
Wilbur was up
for chief of police, OK?

1293
01:10:54,617 --> 01:10:57,453
That's why Nick
couldn't go to the police.

1294
01:10:57,453 --> 01:10:58,912
How do you know Nick?

1295
01:10:58,912 --> 01:11:01,290
Nick is in jail.
He could be there for years.

1296
01:11:01,290 --> 01:11:03,125
Obviously where he belongs.

1297
01:11:03,125 --> 01:11:08,046
Marjorie, you got to help me.
Wilbur's a wreck.

1298
01:11:08,046 --> 01:11:11,049
I can't stand
to see him like this.

1299
01:11:11,049 --> 01:11:13,009
You love him, don't you?

1300
01:11:14,885 --> 01:11:18,013
Yeah, I do.

1301
01:11:18,013 --> 01:11:20,681
I really think
that you should leave.

1302
01:11:20,681 --> 01:11:25,061
Harry, I have something
to tell you...

1303
01:11:25,061 --> 01:11:26,646
privately.

1304
01:11:26,646 --> 01:11:28,064
What is it?

1305
01:11:28,064 --> 01:11:30,608
Harry, I need to talk
to you alone.

1306
01:11:30,608 --> 01:11:32,235
If you have something to say,
just say it now.

1307
01:11:32,235 --> 01:11:33,902
Harry, I need to talk
to you by yourself!

1308
01:11:33,902 --> 01:11:34,903
Just tell me!

1309
01:11:34,903 --> 01:11:36,029
I can't!

1310
01:11:36,029 --> 01:11:38,156
There should be no secrets
in this family!

